snippet.textDisplay:
My thoughts when I saw the ingredients.

Cube up the potatoes, add into a pot of boiling salted water.

Smash and mince a few cloves of garlic top add to some butter in a skillet. Pour over some broccoli and sprinkle on parm cheese before putting it in the oven to roast.

In the same skillet, I'd cook up the bacon. While that's cooking mince the garlic, dice some onion and the apple, and thinly slice the leeks.
Remove the bacon from the skillet, do not drain. Add some caraway seeds and red pepper flakes to the bacon grease. Once the caraway and pepper flakes are fragrant, add apple cider vinegar, sugar, mix together before adding the garlic, onions, and apple. Add salt and pepper. Sweat over medium-low heat.
Wash the spinach, slice the pear into match sticks, add into serving dish. Pour the contents of the skillet into the serving dish and mix well to wilt the spinach. Top with crumbled bacon and parm cheese.

Drain the cooked potatoes. Add butter, salt, pepper, and parsley in pan. Whip with egg beater, adding milk to desired consistency. Fold in thinly sliced leeks.


In the same skillet, melt a generous portion of butter. Salt and pepper the fish. Pan fry the fish over medium high, basting with the browning butter blended with all those other flavors n the skillet.

And if there's time and you're having Barry over, a make a cloud egg.

Have you thought about uploading some of your videos to floatplane.com? You've already made the product and can create a new income stream with it. They know you still need your YT going, there's no algorithm for promoting videos on FP.
It's be cool to see a foodie channel there.
